Superstar, Cristiano Ronaldo has reacted to his side’s Serie A 3-1 defeat to Lazio on Saturday night at the Stadio Olimpico Stadium. Ronaldo scored for Juventus in the 25 minutes of the encounter. But three goals from Luiz Felipe, Sergej Milinkovic-Savic and Felipe Caicedo gave Napoli all three points against MaurIzio Sarri’s men. The defeat against Lazio means Juventus are now two points behind league leaders Inter Milan. Reacting to his side’s defeat against Lazio, Ronaldo in a tweet on his official Twitter page on Sunday, urged his teammates to stay ‘strong together’ until the end of the season. “Keep strong and together until the end! #finoallafine,” Ronaldo posted on Twitter alongside a picture on himself and his teammates celebrating. Ronaldo will now hope to lead Juventus to victory when they host Udinese on December 15 in their next Serie A fixture. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.